.TH mlib_ImageAutoCorrel_Fp 3MLIB "2 Mar 2007" "SunOS 5.11" "mediaLib Library Functions"
.SH NAME
mlib_ImageAutoCorrel_Fp \- auto-correlation of an image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
cc [ \fIflag\fR... ] \fIfile\fR... \fB-lmlib\fR [ \fIlibrary\fR... ]
#include <mlib.h>

\fBmlib_status\fR \fBmlib_ImageAutoCorrel_Fp\fR(\fBmlib_d64 *\fIcorrel\fR,
     \fBconst mlib_image *\fIimg\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIdx\fR, \fBmlib_s32\fR \fIdy\fR);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The \fBmlib_ImageAutoCorrel_Fp()\fR function computes the auto-correlation
of a floating-point image, given an offset.
.sp
.LP
It uses the following equation:
.sp
.in +2
.nf
                  1          w-dx-1 h-dy-1
correl[i] = -------------- *  SUM    SUM  (img[x][y][i] * img[x+dx][y+dy][i])
            (w-dx)*(h-dy)     x=0    y=0
.fi
.in -2

.sp
.LP
where \fBw\fR and \fBh\fR are the width and height of the image,
respectively.
.SH PARAMETERS
.sp
.LP
The function takes the following arguments:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIcorrel\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Pointer to auto-correlation array where size is equal to the number of
channels. \fBcorrel[i]\fR contains the auto-correlation of channel
\fBi\fR.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIimg\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Pointer to image.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIdx\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Displacement in the X direction.
.RE

.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIdy\fR
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Displacement in the Y direction.
.RE

.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
.LP
The function returns \fBMLIB_SUCCESS\fR if successful. Otherwise it returns
\fBMLIB_FAILURE\fR.
